      "id": "task_1756808424071_k0sj7k0dy",
      "title": "Develop comprehensive React component test coverage",
      "description": "Create comprehensive test coverage for React components throughout the application. Current analysis shows severe lacking in component testing with only ~30% coverage vs 80% target.\n\nCOMPONENT AREAS REQUIRING TESTING:\n- Workflow editor components (canvas, blocks, connections)\n- UI components in apps/sim/components/\n- Workspace and folder management components\n- Authentication and user management components\n- Dashboard and analytics components\n- Form components and validation\n- Modal and dialog components\n\nTEST REQUIREMENTS:\n- React Testing Library integration\n- Component rendering and interaction tests\n- Props validation and edge case testing\n- User interaction simulation (clicks, forms, navigation)\n- Accessibility testing integration\n- State management testing (hooks, context)\n- Error boundary and loading state testing\n\nSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n- 90%+ component test coverage\n- All critical user interactions tested\n- Comprehensive accessibility validation\n- Integration with existing test infrastructure\n- Production-ready component testing patterns",
      "mode": "DEVELOPMENT",
      "category": "missing-test",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "pending",
